text: Seveux-Motey is a commune. It is in Bourgogne-Franche-Comté in the Haute-Saône department in east France. The municipality was created on 1 January 2019 and consists of the former communes of Seveux (the seat) and Motey-sur-Saône. == References == Category:2019 establishments in France Category:Communes in Haute-Saône
title: Seveux-Motey
